    "Matsuyama Castle is one of Japan's few surviving original castles and a treasured symbol of Ehime's history and pride. Perched on a hill overlooking the city, the castle grounds are not only a major tourist attraction but also a place of quiet beauty and reflection for locals. Visitors are expected to behave respectfully while exploring the site â€” that means avoiding loud conversations, rough play, or taking silly or disrespectful selfies near historical structures. Walking carefully, appreciating the architecture, and observing signs and rules help preserve the dignity of this cultural landmark. Treating the castle and its surroundings with reverence not only honors the legacy of the past but also ensures that future generations can enjoy its atmosphere of quiet strength and heritage.": "æ¾å±±åŸã¯ç¾å­˜å¤©å®ˆã‚’æŒã¤è²´é‡ãªåŸã§ã€æ„›åª›ã®æ­´å²ã¨èª‡ã‚Šã®è±¡å¾´ã§ã™ã€‚è¦³å…‰åœ°ã§ã‚ã‚‹ã¨åŒæ™‚ã«ã€åœ°å…ƒã®äººã«ã¨ã£ã¦ã‚‚å¤§åˆ‡ãªå ´æ‰€ãªã®ã§ã€å¤§å£°ã‚„ãµã–ã‘ãŸè¡Œå‹•ã€æ­´å²çš„å»ºé€ ç‰©ã®å‰ã§ã®ä¸é©åˆ‡ãªå†™çœŸæ’®å½±ã¯æ§ãˆã¾ã—ã‚‡ã†ã€‚å»ºç‰©ã‚„æ™¯è¦³ã‚’ä¸å¯§ã«æ¥½ã—ã¿ã€ãƒ«ãƒ¼ãƒ«ã‚’å®ˆã‚‹ã“ã¨ã§ã€æœªæ¥ã«ã‚‚ã“ã®é›°å›²æ°—ãŒæ®‹ã›ã¾ã™ã€‚",

